Which Mean Girl are you?
brought to you by Quizilla

I've heard it said
That people come into our lives for a reason
Bringing something we must learn
ANd we are led
To those who help us most to grow
If we let them
And we help them in return
Well, I don't know if I believe that's true
But I know I'm who I am today
Because I knew you
Like a comet pulled from orbit
As it passes a sun
Like a stream that meets a boulder
Halfway through the wood
Who can say if I've been changed for the better?
I have been changed for good
It well may be
That we will never meet again
In this lifetime
So left me say before we part
So much of me
Is made of what I learned from you
You'll be with me
Like a handprint on my heart
And now whatever way our stories end
I know you have re-written mine
By being my friend
Like a ship blown from its mooring
By a wind off the sea
Like a seed dropped by a skybird
In a distant wood
Who can say if I've been changed for the better?
But because I knew you
I have been changed for good
And just to clear the air
I ask forgiveness
For the things I've done you blame me for
But then, I guess we know
There's balme to share
And none of it seems to matter anymore
Who can say if I've been changed for the better?
I do believe I have been changed for the better
And because I knew you
I have been changed for good

lalalala...I'm so excited right about now. It's almost surreal that I'm leaving and not coming back until August. I realized that last night. I was leaving this party, and I realized I was saying goodbye to a bunch of these people until school starts again. I mean, usually, I don't neccessarily see everyone in the summer, but I could see them if I wanted to, and I at least talked to them. I think going to Spain on my own for 6 weeks outweighs not seeing everyone for that amount of time. Tell me if you want my address. Please write :) And tell me if you want me to write to you.

this is to all the girls who are overlooked. who are just friends. who love to laugh and be silly. who flirt and act cute. who keep dreaming. who don't care what they look like and just bum around in sweats and a tshirt. who keep their head up. who aren't afraid or scared. who keep saying it will be ok, even when they don't know. who tell you everything they know and tuly want to make it all better.   who are told "there will always be more fish in the sea." who watch other girls fuck up their life and the guy's but then are still there when the girl comes crying back. who are like a rock. 

This is for the "I really like you, so let's still be friends" comment after you think you're in too deep; this is for never realizing that when you choose friends, you seldom choose those who might make you cry yourself to sleep. This is for the hugs you've received from the girls, for the nights they've reassured you that you are beautiful and intelligent and amazing and loyal and truly worthy of a great guy; this is for the despair you've felt as you've sat crying yourself to sleep in bed. This is for the girls who have been used and abused, who have endured what he was giving because at least he was giving something; this is for the stupidity of the nights we've believed that something was better than nothing, though his something was nothing we'd have ever wanted. This is for the girls who have been satisified with too little and who have learned never to expect anything more: for the girls who don't think that they deserve more, who havent thought it was for them.

this is for all the girls. who say they're done. but deep down still want it. who continue to smile even when they think things can't get any lower than they already are. who stay by your side - always. who tell you a joke. who make fun of you - just to get you to laugh a little. who tell you anything - because they  think it's for the best. who are willing to let loose and have some fun. who tell you you look cute. who make fun of your "country accent". who help you with your homework. who sit with you at lunch. who  truly  just want you to be happy. 

who needs boys anyway?

Okay, so here's a question: what the hell is the fucking point of school? I mean, seriously, at this point, it's just a waste of my time. It sucks ass and it's just effing boring. If you don't know what you're going to do with your life, high school probably won't help you all too much.
Damn, I can't wait till college.
By the way, this is pretty much the me bitching about life journal. Except that probably won't be a lot because I'm a very happy person (except for now). princessmalulu is my happy journal with Princess Martha.

It is SO effing cold in this effing house. I feel like I'm an effing eskimo in effing Alaska. Damn.
So, for Lent, Princess Martha and I gave up ALL sweets except for birthday cake. Not fun. 38 1/2 more days.
I'm so busy for the next 2 months. This weekend is District chorus, next weekend is the Variety Show/4 day weekend, and the weekend after that's recording. Then it's March. Semiformal/recording, Meg's birthday/Dance recital/District competition/Amelia's spring break, my spring break, Beaufort, Amelia/a capella shindig @ William and Mary, and then APRIL, the best month EVER. Choir trip with Nicole and Princess Martha OVER MY BIRTHDAY in DISNEYWORLD!!! Then, A capella Jam (Black, White, and Bling), and the parents finally okayed the party deal, so it's ON. It's about effing time.
March 28. "One Tree Hill" tour at the 9:30 Club. Mark your calendars.
More later
Oh yeah, and if anyone is smart and knows how I can get those little pictures for my live journal or change the fonts, tell me. I'm just technically inept like that.

So, I haven't really updated in a while. Not much is new in my life.
I went to this totally bitchin' party Friday night for Halloween. It was hot. I was most definitely the best fairy princess butterfly there :) AND, my sister took my costume idea and went as Barbara Bush, and her friend went as Jenna.
I got my quarter grades, and it's all good for me! Hopefully, this will get my parents off my back (some).
Been busy doing lots of singing. It's fun though. I heart a capella! But I have an audition in 2 weeks for district 12, so I'm nervous about that.
I'm really, really, really tired right now. Nicole knows JUST how tired I am. Hehehe...
Quote of the day: "It's SO COLD in here! I feel like I go to a school for eskimos!"- Me
More later. Hope you all are having bitchin' lives, AND that you all start saying "bitchin'."
---LM
(by the way, "bitchin'" is a good thing)

Okay, so here's a list of al lthe exciting things I did this weekend (because I'm sure you all won't be able to sleep unless you know every little detail of my wonderful life):
1. Picked up my sister from W&M.
2. Ate quiche.
3. Went to the mall.
4. Saw a hot guy.
5. Went to Temmil.
6. Went to my cousin's house.
7. Stayed up until 1 to watch Desperate Housewives.
8. Went to the mall AGAIN.
9. Went to Target.
So that is my WONDERFUL exciting long weekend, and it's not even over!
So here's my question: How is it that people can spell their own names wrong? Like me; I spelled my name "Luccy," and my friend Megan spelled her name "Mean." How can people be so stupid sometimes?
More later :)
